HashMap<K, T, H, C> Class

HashMap is a container of key-value pairs that are organized in a hashtable. The keys need not to be ordered.

Syntax

public class HashMap<K, T, H, C>;

Template Parameters

K The type of the key.
T The type of the value.
H = Hasher<K> The hash function. Default is Hasher<K> .
C = EqualTo<K> The key comparioson operation. Default is EqualTo<K> .

Constraint

K is Semiregular and T is Semiregular and HashFunction <H , K > and C is Relation and C .Domain is K

Insert(const T& value) Member Function

Inserts an element to the hash set if it's not already there. If the element was inserted to the hash set, returns a pair consisting of an iterator to it and true, otherwise an equal element was already in the hash set, so return a pair consisting of an iterator to an existing element and false.

Map is an associative array of key-value pairs sorted by the keys.

Value The type of the value.

Insert(const Pair<Key, Value>& value) Member Function

Inserts a key-value pair to the map if the key is not already found from the map. If the key-value pair was inserted to the map, returns a pair consisting of an iterator to it and true, otherwise a key-value pair with an equal key was already in the map, so return a pair consisting of an iterator to an existing key-value pair and false.
